item.title: Help me with auto restarter
item.dc:creator: @Helbound Helbound
item.description:
@Helbound wrote:

[quote=“p00nscape, post:5, topic:168254”]free porn =][/quote] [size=20pt][center]QUIT WITH YOUR DAMN SPAM!!![/center][br][br][size=1]Posted on: December 27, 2007, 03:34:56 PM[/size][hr][quote=“thomas121794, post:6, topic:168254”]ok when i did that it didint restart my server… and my run.bat dont work right

[quote]Error occurred during initialization of VM
java/lang/NoClassDefFoundError: java/lang/Object
Press any key to continue . . .[/quote]

i get this error[/quote]

Could you check to see if you have a batch file named voule.bat in the same folder as your voule auto restarter is in? Because the voule auto restarter executable file only is used as the timer, but the vould.bat batch file is what the executable file launches to restart the server.

If you don’t have it, or just can’t find it, create a new text file, and open it up. Then copy and paste this inside the text file:

@echo off cls echo Restarted using Voule's Auto Restarter tskill java /a echo Restarting server cls echo Restarted using Voule's Auto Restarter title Server java -Xmx1024m -cp .;./jython.jar;./MySql/mysql-connector-java-3.0.17-ga-bin.jar server cls echo Connection Ended! pause exit

Then save that file as voule.bat.
Now try running the restarter again. And if it still doesn’t work, tell me, and I will give you the download link for the version that should work.
